The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | Fraud slur on councillor
                                                                                                                         3                                                                                      Fraud slur on councillor
          A STAFF REPORTER                              
	Police on Thursday registered a complaint against Congress councillor Suman Singh, who has been accused of siphoning off Rs 1 lakh from the state governments Old Age Pension Fund.        
	Chitpur police station registered the case against the councillor of ward 6 following a court order.        
	Police said more than 40 elderly residents had moved Sealdah court alleging that Singh had embezzled around Rs 1 lakh of pension funds and was denying them their dues.        
	The civic body is the nodal agency of the fund and it is the councillors responsibility to hand over the money to the beneficiaries. Deputy commissioner (north) Biswarup Ghosh said a probe had been ordered.                                                                                                                                                          
